5:
Whoa... It's so cold I can see my
breath.
9:
It's definitely on the chilly side.
Winter's finally here.
15:
You've got another meeting coming
up, don't you, Mr. Takamori? Aren't
you working yourself too hard?
20:
I've got something to hash out with
Adjudicus. And I don't know about
"too" hard—today's a relatively light
day.
24:
Stella and I are about to head to the
academy. Headmistress Nihilyana
has called on us. A matter related to
the Purgers, by the sound of it.
29:
Is it really okay for me to sit around
doing nothing...?
33:
Of course. Why, just look at Nimbus!
That's all he does. Oh, but please
don't pick up his drinking habit.
37:
Take this time to recharge. You're
going to need the energy later on.
42:
I guess that leaves me time to do
some cooking. I know just the recipe
to pull out.
48:
Your signature red soup.
I'll make sure to come home as
quickly as possible.
53:
Great. I'll go do some shopping,
then. Mr. Takamori, thanks for all
your hard work.
65:
Hah! Incredible! Those two have
really outdone themselves!
69:
It's all thanks to the peerless
acumen of my dear Love and
Renoir! Look at all these tools and
gadgets they've given me!
72:
Why, I've half the mind to just up
and adopt those two! I'd make a
great adoptive mother, don't you
think?
76:
...If we could move on to the topic at
hand. What does this have to do
with the tissue samples we provided
you?
81:
Ah, right. That! Well, those ended up
yielding some positively fascinating
results!
84:
You see, it turns out that the two of
you and that Purger back there are
more or less identical in
composition.
88:
Let me be more precise: a part of
you possesses the same capacity
for deception.
98:
Yes. Pretense. Camouflage. Lying. It's
almost as if you're... wearing
something to conceal your true self.
101:
A curse, maybe. One which has
warped your very form. That's
precisely what I want to investigate
further.
106:
But... I am still a human, am I not? Or
at least, I was originally.
111:
Superficially, yes. But I'm talking
about something much deeper
within you. Think of it as... a cocoon
around your soul.
121:
Or, conversely, perhaps it could
manifest as free will? I have quite
the eye for matters like these, you
see.
124:
The problem is, directly touching the
soul can be perilous. I'd hoped to
use you as an intermediary,
Stella—since you and Light share the
same composition.
133:
Hold on, now. Surely there's
something I can do to help as well!
138:
I'm afraid you won't do—your view of
the world is far too... rigid and fixed.
Instead, why don't you act as our
anchor? Just stand by and watch us
as we work.
149:
No need to worry. If things go south,
I'll be the one who bears the
consequences—and melts away. Oh
well. Ready to begin?
155:
O all-devouring darkness,
O hidden palace that spurns the
brilliance of the sun.
158:
That sounds like what Gram always
says.
163:
Haha. That would be because we
came up with this incantation
together.
167:
How about we expand upon it:
O all-illuminating light!
176:
O false dichotomy which conceals
the truth. Melt away thy bifold
pretense! Melt away the lie!
181:
Swim the tides of chaos, and laugh
unto the void. Then ask thyself
whence life draws its myriad
meanings!
185: Within thyself, what dost thou see?
189:
No need for concern. We're dealing
with a mere puppet, after all. It lacks
the power to change my reality.
Now, tell me, did you see?
196:
We... are connected to the Origin
Dragon.
211:
It's coming from the academy...
It couldn't be—
216:
What are these things doing down
here?!
